    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "&ldquo;Suffer the little children to come unto Me, and forbid them not: for of such is the kingdom of heaven.&rdquo; These precious words are to be cherished, not only by every mother, but by every father as well. These words are an <span class=\"page-break\" data-page=\"276\"></span> encouragement to parents to press their children into His notice, to ask in the name of Christ that the Father may let His blessing rest upon their entire family. Not only are the best beloved to receive particular attention, but also the restless, wayward children, who need careful training and tender guidance.<sup class=\"chapterendnote\"><a class=\"chapterendnote\">6<span class=\"chapterendnote\"><span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"ST 8-13-1896\" data-link=\"820.13604\">The Signs of the Times, August 13, 1896</span>.</span></a></sup>",
